Program: Discovery
Title: LIGO - going where no observatory has gone before
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxlr
Last Broadcast Date: 02 February 2000
Report on the Laser Interferometer Gravitational-Wave Observatory (LIGO). In Washington State US, the largest in a global network of observatories designed to detect the faintest objects in the universe including gravity waves from black holes and neutron stars.